  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This synthetic adversarial package intentionally embeds a Critical weakener (W-EP-01: orphan claim with no prov:wasDerivedFrom) and a High weakener (W-AL-01: ValidationResults lacking hasUncertaintyQuantification) on the same UnitOfAssurance to trigger COMPOUND-01 detection.",
